# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Mouse2Joy .gitignore
# Based on the GitHub-curated VisualStudio.gitignore template, trimmed to what
# this solution might realistically encounter and extended for Rider/JetBrains.
#
# IMPORTANT: the vendored Interception DLL and its SHA-256 pin must remain
# tracked. They live under src/Mouse2Joy.App/native/x64/ and are intentionally
# NOT matched by any rule below (no broad *.dll ignore — only build outputs).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Build results
[Dd]ebug/
[Dd]ebugPublic/
[Rr]elease/
[Rr]eleases/
x64/
x86/
[Ww][Ii][Nn]32/
[Aa][Rr][Mm]/
[Aa][Rr][Mm]64/
bld/
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
[Ll]og/
[Ll]ogs/
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/publish/
[Pp]ublish/

# Vendored native dependencies — must remain tracked. The `x64/` rule above
# (intended for MSBuild platform output) otherwise swallows this folder.
!src/Mouse2Joy.App/native/x64/
!src/Mouse2Joy.App/native/x64/**

## .NET / MSBuild
project.lock.json
project.fragment.lock.json
artifacts/
*.binlog
*.tlog

## Test results
[Tt]est[Rr]esult*/
[Bb]uild[Ll]og.*
*.VisualState.xml
TestResult.xml
nunit-*.xml
*.trx
coverage*.json
coverage*.xml
coverage*.info
*.coverage
*.coveragexml

## Visual Studio
.vs/
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.userprefs
*.sln.docstates
*.sln.iml
*.psess
*.vsp
*.vspx
*.sap

## ReSharper / Rider / JetBrains
.idea/
_ReSharper*/
*.[Rr]e[Ss]harper
*.DotSettings.user

## VS Code (keep shared workspace config, ignore local caches)
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
*.code-workspace
.history/

## NuGet
*.nupkg
*.snupkg
**/[Pp]ackages/*
!**/[Pp]ackages/build/
*.nuget.props
*.nuget.targets
.nuget/

## ClickOnce / Publish profiles
*.publishsettings
publishProfiles/
PublishScripts/

## Code analysis / profiling
*.dotCover
*.dotTrace
BenchmarkDotNet.Artifacts/

## Backup & generated
*.bak
*.cache
*.tmp
*.log
*.swp
*~

## OS junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
ehthumbs_vista.db
desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

## Windows installer / native build artefacts (project does not ship these,
## but keep the doors closed in case a future packaging script lands here)
*.msi
*.msm
*.msp
*.cab
